1
00:01:21,330 --> 00:01:27,080
[Love Endures]

2
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:29,800
[Episode 3]

3
00:01:36,070 --> 00:01:37,120
Thinking about it,

4
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:39,270
I'm very confident

5
00:01:40,070 --> 00:01:41,350
that he's pretending to lose his memory.

6
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:45,240
What if

7
00:01:45,240 --> 00:01:46,120
it is real?

8
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,200
Well, if he lost his memory,

9
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,960
he won't recognize us anymore.

10
00:01:53,710 --> 00:01:55,680
I don't think that's real either.

11
00:01:57,270 --> 00:01:58,790
But why would he pretend?

12
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:01,630
Is there a possibility it's because

13
00:02:01,910 --> 00:02:04,430
Madam Wang and Mr. Jiang
are always on business trips?

14
00:02:04,430 --> 00:02:06,350
He wanted to keep them using this way.

15
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,880
Pretending to lose his memory?

16
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,160
Looks like he is acting a drama with me.

17
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:14,510
Let's see how I'm going
to expose you today.

18
00:02:22,790 --> 00:02:25,000
Jiang Yi!

19
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:28,880
My poor Jiang Yi!

20
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,950
Aunt's here to see you.

21
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:34,440
Aunt.

22
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,070
Am I your eldest aunt

23
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:37,720
or the youngest aunt?

24
00:02:39,510 --> 00:02:41,880
I don't really remember.

25
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:46,280
It's okay, my nephew.

26
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,440
Look what I brought for you.

27
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:48,760
Your favourite beef stew

28
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,880
and stir-fried vegetables
with fried dace.

29
00:02:51,830 --> 00:02:53,070
I don't remember

30
00:02:53,070 --> 00:02:54,830
I love these either.

31
00:02:55,350 --> 00:02:57,110
Then I'm sure you don't remember

32
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:59,350
your favourite tomato juice either.

33
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,390
Drink up, my nephew.

34
00:03:05,390 --> 00:03:06,830
It's your favourite juice.

35
00:03:06,830 --> 00:03:08,670
Drink up, my nephew.

36
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:11,350
Thank you, Aunt.

37
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:25,320
I can't believe it.

38
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:26,790
He really drank it.

39
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:29,070
He really lost his memory.

40
00:03:33,110 --> 00:03:33,950
Thank you, Aunt.

41
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:36,760
It tasted really good.

42
00:03:42,510 --> 00:03:43,790
Come on. Eat more.

43
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:45,040
Eating more might help you to remember.

44
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,230
Eat more.

45
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,160
How's it?

46
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,280
Can you remember this time?

47
00:03:53,630 --> 00:03:54,830
There's nothing else we can do.

48
00:03:54,830 --> 00:03:56,160
We'll have to use the last strategy.

49
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:57,350
Huang Yingzi!

50
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:05,200
After our repeated research,

51
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,510
you lost your memory

52
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:07,790
the moment you fell.

53
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,390
For the few days after that incident,

54
00:04:09,390 --> 00:04:10,480
you remember everything.

55
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,110
So your symptoms indicated

56
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:13,830
a kind of persistent memory loss.

57
00:04:14,110 --> 00:04:15,000
You have lost your memory

58
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,800
before the men's 400 meters.

59
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,950
All of them.

60
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:18,880
Then?

61
00:04:19,590 --> 00:04:20,590
I can only tell

62
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:22,270
you're quite a lucky guy

63
00:04:22,590 --> 00:04:24,510
to have met us as your friends.

64
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:26,240
You're like a hard drive now.

65
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,830
The data inside your brain is gone.

66
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:29,070
But it doesn't matter.

67
00:04:29,070 --> 00:04:30,000
Take your time.

68
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,360
Let's make a copy

69
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,760
and insert into your brain.

70
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:34,320
I'm such a genius!

71
00:04:36,030 --> 00:04:37,150
How to make a copy?

72
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:39,360
In the whole Hangtian City,

73
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:41,240
we are the people who know you best.

74
00:04:41,630 --> 00:04:43,880
It took me three days

75
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,710
to compress the 17 years of your life

76
00:04:45,710 --> 00:04:47,030
into

77
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:49,200
this notebook worth only three yuan.

78
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,200
I wrote "The Life of Jiang Yi" for you.

79
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,030
Next,

80
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:55,760
I will read it aloud to you.

81
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:56,270
You only need to

82
00:04:56,590 --> 00:04:57,440
listen carefully

83
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:58,950
and remember attentively.

84
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,800
When I'm done reading,

85
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,470
your memory of 17 years will recover.

86
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:04,680
At the same time,

87
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:06,440
Mingyu will record in real time

88
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:09,510
and play it on Hangtian City
High School's radio station,

89
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:11,200
on repeat for the whole day.

90
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,630
Let's start.

91
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:15,030
Your name is Jiang Yi.

92
00:05:15,030 --> 00:05:17,000
You were born on February 18, 1990,

93
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,950
in the beautiful Hangtian City.

94
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,880
During your senior year of kindergarten,

95
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,710
you wore a spittoon as a hat,

96
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:24,360
telling you want to practice iron head.

97
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,000
I was a kid

98
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
and really believed
that you were talented in martial arts.

99
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,390
One day I told you

100
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,150
there was a big spittoon

101
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:34,030
in the kindergarten teacher's office.

102
00:05:34,030 --> 00:05:36,360
If you were able to use it
to practice iron head,

103
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,390
it would be a rapid progress.

104
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,830
So, during your lunch break,

105
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:43,030
you snuck into the office,

106
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:45,120
picked the big spittoon up,

107
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,680
and put it on your head.

108
00:05:47,510 --> 00:05:48,950
You didn't notice

109
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:51,360
there was something in the spittoon,

110
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:53,630
spat out by Teacher Wang.

111
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,680
Enough!

112
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,240
Stop it.

113
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,320
Idiot.

114
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,360
You faked it!

115
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,920
You were just pretending!

116
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,270
By the way,

117
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:11,150
there was nothing in the spittoon.

118
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,240
"The Life of Jiang Yi"?

119
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,070
Rip it up!

120
00:06:14,470 --> 00:06:15,510
I've already finished writing it.

121
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:16,920
I'm not going to rip it!

122
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:17,760
No way!

123
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:18,880
Give it to me.

124
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,000
Give it to me!

125
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:21,510
Here!

126
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:22,680
Give it to me!

127
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,630
I am warning you!

128
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:24,510
Give it to me! Faster!

129
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,120
So, why on earth did you come out

130
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,240
with that silly idea?

131
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:29,800
Because I'm really scared

132
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,030
that you would forget about us.

133
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,360
By the way,

134
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,830
that "The Life of Jiang Yi",

135
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:36,710
where is it now?

136
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,270
I don't know.

137
00:06:38,630 --> 00:06:40,800
I guess someone destroyed it.

138
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,240
Why would I keep that such thing?

139
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,710
But there are a few things

140
00:06:48,270 --> 00:06:49,710
that I've been keeping with me.

141
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:50,880
Wait a minute.

142
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:06,360
For my 17th birthday,

143
00:07:06,710 --> 00:07:07,360
do you guys still remember

144
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,680
what you got me?

145
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:24,120
Happy birthday to you!

146
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:30,830
Thank you guys!

147
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,360
Where are my presents?

148
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,360
Thank you, Zhuang Yuan!

149
00:07:39,710 --> 00:07:40,830
(Whenever Huang Yingzi shows this card,)

150
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,630
(I, Zhuang Yuan, will grant
a wish of hers.)

151
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:47,200
Thank you.

152
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:49,630
Thank you, Mingyu.

153
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:57,030
(Whenever Huang Yingzi shows this card,)

154
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,200
(I, Fang Mingyu,
will grant a wish of hers.)

155
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:34,040
I officially announce

156
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:35,470
the Six of Hangtian City

157
00:08:35,470 --> 00:08:37,560
is disbanded today!

158
00:08:38,350 --> 00:08:39,070
I'm leaving.

159
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,160
I'm leaving for real.

160
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,070
For real!

161
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:48,640
Leaving!

162
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:49,710
I'm leaving!

163
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,110
I'm really leaving!

164
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:53,920
Why is no one stopping me?

165
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,230
Here I come.

166
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,640
Yingzi,

167
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,070
this is our idea.

168
00:08:58,070 --> 00:08:59,830
We've discussed for a long time

169
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:01,280
and came out with this idea.

170
00:09:02,590 --> 00:09:03,750
Don't leave.

171
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:08,470
You guys worked it out together?

172
00:09:09,070 --> 00:09:11,230
You guys are so clever.

173
00:09:11,950 --> 00:09:13,470
It's mainly because
your previous birthdays

174
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:14,920
were too wonderful.

175
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,520
We were out of ideas.

176
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:17,280
However,

177
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,320
think about it.

178
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,590
Let's say I became a great scholar,

179
00:09:20,590 --> 00:09:21,950
Mingyu became a CEO,

180
00:09:21,950 --> 00:09:23,640
not to mention Yifei and Guan Chao,

181
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,750
there will be people all over the street
chasing them for autographs.

182
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:26,400
When the time comes,

183
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,680
we can get you anything

184
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:28,680
worth more than anything
you could get now.

185
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:29,590
You're right.

186
00:09:29,590 --> 00:09:30,950
I understood.

187
00:09:30,950 --> 00:09:31,750
So the four of you

188
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:33,470
will be earning more money.

189
00:09:33,470 --> 00:09:34,230
Am I right?

190
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:36,470
What about you?

191
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:39,160
Me?

192
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:41,440
As long as I don't need to marry you,

193
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,350
I can do everything.

194
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,470
What did I hear?

195
00:09:46,470 --> 00:09:47,830
Not wanting to marry me?

196
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:48,680
You made it sound like

197
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:49,640
I would have a crush on you.

198
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,070
So what?

199
00:09:50,070 --> 00:09:51,830
Don't tell me you have a crush
on Zhu Baoming.

200
00:09:52,749 --> 00:09:53,589
Someone is jealous!

201
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:55,070
Why not tell you have a crush
on Chao Tingting?

202
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:55,920
What's wrong with Chao Tingting?

203
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,109
She has quite beautiful eyes.

204
00:09:57,109 --> 00:09:57,519
More beautiful than yours.

205
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,520
Say that again.

206
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:58,950
What do you want?

207
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:00,040
Did you mean Chao Tingting is cute?

208
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:00,950
Not only is she cute,

209
00:10:00,950 --> 00:10:02,440
but she is also a fan of Stefanie Sun!

210
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:02,710
You...

211
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:03,680
Chao Tingting! Chao Tingting!

212
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:05,070
Zhu Baoming! Zhu Baoming! Zhu Baoming!

213
00:10:05,070 --> 00:10:06,870
Chao Tingting! Chao Tingting!
Chao Tingting!

214
00:10:06,870 --> 00:10:07,440
Zhu...

215
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:08,870
Don't run away!

216
00:10:08,870 --> 00:10:09,750
You get over here!

217
00:10:11,830 --> 00:10:12,870
Stop right there!

218
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:18,470
Whenever it is and wherever we are,

219
00:10:19,070 --> 00:10:20,950
as soon as I show this card,

220
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:23,230
you will fulfill one of my wishes.

221
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:26,160
I wonder if it still counts.

222
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:41,160
Among the six of us,

223
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:43,280
only Guan Chao stayed in Hangtian City.

224
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:44,280
These few years,

225
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,400
he took care
of his grandma all by himself

226
00:10:47,070 --> 00:10:49,320
and even our parents

227
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,160
and family members.

228
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:53,230
He's getting married now.

229
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,560
He's going to accomplish something big
in his life.

230
00:10:56,350 --> 00:10:57,870
I'm sure he'd want us, his good friends,

231
00:10:57,870 --> 00:10:58,920
to go back.

232
00:11:00,070 --> 00:11:02,470
If this card still counts,

233
00:11:03,470 --> 00:11:04,470
I hope

234
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:07,040
you can go back to Hangtian City
with me

235
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,990
to attend Guan Chao's wedding.

236
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:10,870
I know.

237
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:12,400
We're all grown up now.

238
00:11:12,830 --> 00:11:14,800
We have our own things to do.

239
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,280
We also have our own difficulties.

240
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,870
You don't have to answer me right away.

241
00:11:17,870 --> 00:11:19,110
But don't refuse so fast.

242
00:11:20,230 --> 00:11:22,160
The wedding's a week away anyway.

243
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,590
I'll be waiting for your answers.

244
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:42,440
That's the end of my presentation.

245
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,470
Thank you.

246
00:11:43,830 --> 00:11:45,920
From your proposal,

247
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,990
we've found multiple data errors.

248
00:11:47,990 --> 00:11:50,200
Hence, it's impossible to predict

249
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:50,800
the physical outcome.

250
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:51,440
This is impossible.

251
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:53,280
These mistakes are not allowed

252
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,590
in a qualified doctoral thesis.

253
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:56,470
After our discussion,

254
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:57,200
we have decided

255
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,750
that your defense for this proposal

256
00:11:58,750 --> 00:11:59,590
is rejected.

257
00:12:01,710 --> 00:12:02,400
Mr. Feng,

258
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,200
were you looking for me?

259
00:12:03,710 --> 00:12:04,400
Mingyu,

260
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:06,560
I need to tell you something.

261
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:07,640
Guo Kai's department

262
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,350
requires several systems engineers.

263
00:12:09,350 --> 00:12:10,400
I'm sorry to trouble you, Ms. Fang.

264
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:11,440
You're welcome.

265
00:12:11,830 --> 00:12:13,320
During your weekend business trip
to Hong Kong,

266
00:12:13,590 --> 00:12:15,560
greet Mr. Xu at the head office for me.

267
00:12:16,590 --> 00:12:17,400
Mr. Feng,

268
00:12:17,870 --> 00:12:20,350
I want to take this weekend off.

269
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,870
I have to attend a friend's wedding.

270
00:12:23,590 --> 00:12:24,590
Initially,

271
00:12:25,590 --> 00:12:26,990
I secured a spot for you

272
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:28,200
for graduate studies.

273
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,070
But who would have thought

274
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:32,070
you didn't even pass your proposal?

275
00:12:32,830 --> 00:12:33,950
This opportunity,

276
00:12:34,350 --> 00:12:35,680
I'm afraid I can't secure it for you.

277
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:37,750
Sir,

278
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,110
I'm sorry.

279
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:41,520
There's no point
in saying sorry right now.

280
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:42,950
Please,

281
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,320
don't take your future for granted.

282
00:12:48,710 --> 00:12:49,520
Zhuang Yuan.

283
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:51,920
Your father passed away at a young age.

284
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,990
Your mother brought you up by herself

285
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,520
and paid for your studies,

286
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:57,750
all the way here.

287
00:12:58,110 --> 00:12:58,590
I know.

